        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 27</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num027-P260v-L3_trl" n="3"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.004.026.trl.xml#Num026-P260v-L3_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And the daughters
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             of Zelophehad, son of Hepher, son of Gilead, son of Machir,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             son of Manasseh, by the families of Manasseh the son of Joseph, came
                            forward.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             And these are the names of his daughters: Mahlah, Noah, and Hoglah,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             and Milcah, and Tirzah.</l>
                        <l n="2">And they stood
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             before Moses, and before Eleazar the priest, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             before the princes and all the congregation, by the door
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             of the tent of meeting, saying,</l>
                        <l n="3">‘Our father died
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             in the wilderness, and he was not among the congregation who were
                            gathered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             against the Lord, in the congregation of Korah, because he died for his
                            own sin.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             And he had no sons.</l>
                        <l n="4">Why
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             should the name of our father be taken away from among his family,
                            because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             he has no son? Give to us a possession among the brothers
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             of our father.’</l>
                        <l n="5">And Moses brought their
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             cause before the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="6">And the Lord spoke
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <l n="7">‘The daughters of Zelophehad speak right:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             you shall surely give them a possession of a portion
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             among their father’s brothers, and you shall cause
                            <milestone unit="page" n="261r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             the portion of their father to pass to them.</l>
                        <l n="8">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             you shall speak to the children of Israel, saying, “If a man dies, and
                            has no son,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             then you shall cause his portion to pass to his daughter.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="9">And if he has no daughter, then you shall cause
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             his portion to pass to his brethren. <supplied reason="lost" /></l>
                        <l n="10"><supplied reason="lost"> And if he has no brothers, then you shall
                                give his portion to his father’s brothers.</supplied></l>
                        <l n="11">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             if his father has no brothers, then you shall give
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             his portion to his closest relative of his family,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             and he shall inherit it. And it shall be to the children of Israel
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             a statute of judgment, as the Lord commanded Moses.”’</l>
                        <l n="12">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             And the Lord said to Moses, ‘Get up
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-027-seg001_trl" />to this mountain
                            of encampments<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-027-seg001_trl"
                                 /><ref n="1" target="#Num-027-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> and see
                            the land
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             which I have given to the children of Israel.</l>
                        <l n="13">And you shall see
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             it, and you shall be gathered to your people, you as well, as
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             Aaron, your brother, was gathered,</l>
                        <l n="14">Because you rebelled against
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             me and you did not do my word in the desert of Zin, in the quarrel
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             of the congregation, to show my holiness by giving
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             water from the rock in their sight.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             That is the water <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-027-seg002_trl"
                             />of quarrel<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-027-seg002_trl" /><ref
                                n="2" target="#Num-027-fn2_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> of Kadesh of
                            the wilderness of Zin.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="15">And Moses spoke to the Lord, saying,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="16">‘Let the Lord, the God of the spirits of the living beings of all
                            flesh, appoint
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             a man as a superior over the congregation:</l>
                        <l n="17">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="261v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             Who may go out in front of them, and who may come in in front of them,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             and who may bring them out, and who may bring them in, so that the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             congregation of the Lord may not be like sheep that do not have a
                            shepherd.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="18">And the Lord said to Moses, ‘Take
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             Joshua, son of Nun, a man in whom is the inspiration, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             reach out your hand over him.</l>
                        <l n="19">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             And stand him before Eleazar, the priest, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             before all the congregation, and appoint him to be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             superior in their sight.</l>
                        <l n="20">And you shall put
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             some of your honour on him, so that all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             the congregation of the children of Israel may hear.</l>
                        <l n="21">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             he shall stand before Eleazar, the priest, who shall ask him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             after the |required| manner of Urim before the Lord. According to his
                            word
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             they shall go out, and according to his word they shall come in,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             he and all the children of Israel <addSpan spanTo="#Num-027-add001_trl"
                                 /><emph>with him</emph><anchor type="addSpan"
                                xml:id="Num-027-add001_trl" /> and all the congregation.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="22">And Moses did as the Lord commanded him.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             And he took Joshua and stood him before
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             Eleazar, the priest, and before all the congregation.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="23">And he reached out his hands over him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             and appointed him to be superior, as the
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num027-P261v-L21_trl" n="21"
                                next="ADub.III.73.004.028.trl.xml#Num028-P261v-L21_trl" />
                             Lord had spoken by the prophecy of Moses.</l>
                    </ab>
